Context("Numeric");
#given
$theta = random(30,45,1);
$vB = 30*5/18;
$vA = 100*5/18;
$thetaR = $theta*pi/180;

#image scale
$imgScale = .4;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*1210;
$height = $imgScale*1510;

#computation
$omega = -$vB/10;
$vi = -$vA*sin($thetaR) - $vB - $omega* 20;
$vj = $vA*cos($thetaR);

#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.01);

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "UBC-DYN-17-005.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A police car maintains a constant speed of [`V_B=30`] [`km/h`] and follows the path of a circular arc with its center at point [`C`], as shown in the figure. Car [`A`] drives [`\theta=[$theta]^{\circ}`] west of north at [`V_A=100`] [`km/h`]. Calculate the velocity of Car [`A`] measured relative to the officer in the police car.

[`v_{A/B}=`] [______]{"$vi"}[`i`] [`+`] [______]{"$vj"}[`j`] [`m/s`]  

END_PGML

